#Twitter Network
Code for generating an nth degree network of followers / following from twitter.

Usage: python -W ignore new_twitter_crawler.py --User=DjPauli_G --Degree=2 --Pickle=true --Text=true -- >DjPauli_G.out 2>DjPauli_G.progress

 python -W ignore new_twitter_crawler.py --User=DjPauli_G --Degree=2 --Pickle=xxxx.pickle --Text=xxxx.out 2>DjPauli_G.progress


-W ignore: Ignore python SSL warnings generated from tweepy API
--User: the root node
--Degree: Degree of following
--Pickle: Whether or not to save the final result as a pickled python adjacency list
--Text: Whether or not to output the final result to stanard output in the following form:
2>file.progress: Redirect standard output to file.progress for tracking progress



(user) : (list, of, followers, seperated, by, commas) \n
...

e.g:
user1: user2, user3
user2: user1
user3: user1
